● The scoring system operates on two synchronized layers (Python backend, JavaScript frontend) with the same rules:

  Points per Action:

  - Regular food (snake_game.py:194, game.js:404/531): 10 × pointsMultiplier
  pointsMultiplier starts at 1.0 and can be set by power-ups (rainbow → 2.0)
  - Bonus food (snake_game.py:264, game.js:166): flat +50 regardless of multipliers
  - Mirror snake collects food (snake_game.py:219, game.js:404): also awards 10 × pointsMultiplier (backend only; mirror logic not yet in JS)

  High Score Tracking:

  - In-memory: SnakeGame.high_score (Python) and SnakeGame.highScore (JS)
  - Update occurs in three places:
    a. start_game() — before resetting (snake_game.py:123)
    b. reset_game() — same check (snake_game.py:142)
    c. gameOver() — after death (game.js:478/585)
  - Persistence: only the client saves to localStorage under key 'snakeHighScore' (game.js:480/587).
  Server resets high_score to 0 on each new SnakeGame instance; no database or file storage.

  Combo System (unrelated to score but affects bonus food spawning):
  - consecutive_foods increments on every regular food eat
  - At 5 consecutive foods a bonus fruit spawns; counter resets

  The server can return current score and high_score via get_game_state(), but the live high-score value visible in the browser is purely local and lost on hard refresh unless saved in localStorage.
